description.narrative: Combat international narcotics production and trafficking; reduce the cultivation and production of drugs; prevent the resurgence of drug production; and limit the public health effects of the drug trade through international drug control and demand reduction, prevention and treatment projects.

This award strives to combat international narcotics production and trafficking; reduce the cultivation and production of drugs; prevent the resurgence of drug production; and limit the public health effects of the drug trade trhough international drug control and demand reduction, prevention and treatment projects. More specifically, this includes A new task order award for the INL/Peru Ports and Customs Program specifically addresses the interdiction of illicit narcotics at ports of entry in Peru.. Modification to realign funding from CLIN005 and CLIN006 to CLIN001 and CLIN004 to cover final deliverables..
